# Stitch → POXY WORLD (safe redesign)

## Never touch

- `supabase.createClient`, `STORAGE_URL`, RLS-facing table/column names
- `handleAuth`, `setupAuthStateListener`, `bootApp`, `showPage`, economy/case weights
- Storage paths: `avatars/{userId}.*` — not `avatars/avatar`
- Existing element **ids** used by JS (`getElementById`, `$('...')`)

## Allowed

- Add CSS at end of `<style>` or new classes (prefer `poxy-` prefix for Stitch-only rules)
- Replace **inner HTML** of a single container after mapping Stitch markup to existing hooks
- Visual tokens from `DESIGN.md`

## Before finishing any Stitch merge

1. Confirm `bootApp()` still runs last and auth button uses `addEventListener`
2. Grep for duplicate `const $` or early calls to `$()` before its definition
3. User test checklist: login → profile avatar → collection (regular + club card menu) → one case

## If Stitch returns React/Tailwind

Convert to vanilla CSS; do not add a bundler or replace `index.html` wholesale.
